# User-scope preset policy for snow desktops. Applied at image build by
# mkosi (`systemctl --global preset-all`) and again on first boot by
# preset-global.service. Units not listed here fall through to systemd's
# default-enable, which covers gnome-remote-desktop, pipewire, podman, etc.
#
# These replace the manual symlink surgery that used to live in
# snow.postinst.chroot: mkosi runs --global preset-all AFTER postinst
# scripts, so a postinst `rm` of an enablement symlink was silently undone
# by the later default-enable (observed shipped: BOTH gnome-remote-desktop
# variants enabled despite their mutual Conflicts=).

# The headless variant declares Conflicts=gnome-remote-desktop.service;
# only the non-headless variant may be enabled on a desktop image.
disable gnome-remote-desktop-headless.service

# rygel (UPnP/DLNA media server) is deliberately not autostarted: an
# always-on media server is a surprising desktop default.
disable rygel.service
